OL,3,CInheritance tax change affects 'one
OL,4,Cthird' of NI farms
OL,6,FBut the NFU says many family farms
OL,7,Fhave a high notional asset value, but
OL,8,Fvery low income and liquidity, which
OL,9,Fmeans that the vast majority of owners
OL,10,Fwould be unable to meet the
OL,11,Finheritance tax charges, without
OL,12,Fselling assets.
OL,14,FHowever, the Government continued to
OL,15,Finsist the vast majority of farmers
OL,16,Fwill still be able to "pass the family
OL,17,Ffarm down to their children",
OL,18,Ffollowing the meeting.
